<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="524" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.115G82/37</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-12">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1407. Your 1903, 8th. Attorneys for <persName corresp="#p_W1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Wilhelmina</hi>
                                </persName> inform Department that April 10 they cabled their
                                representative, London, authorizing acceptance in substance British
                                proposal, leaving details to him. They request proceedings be
                                expedited. You are authorized render all possible assistance.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>